ings to appear in a WC Finalrefhttphomepagesenterpriseneteico1930htmfinal History of the World Cup Part One 1930 UruguayrefEvaristo was christened Marino but later changed his name to MarioHe played for Sportivo Palermo Club Atltico Independiente and Boca Juniors in Argentina he was part of the Boca team that won the Primera Division Argentina 1931 the first professional champions of ArgentinaLater in his career he moved to Europe where he played for Genoa CFC in Italy and for OGC NiceNice and Antibes in FranceWith his brother Juan EvaristoJuan  he was in charge of Bocas youth academies for more than 30 yearsrefhttpwwwhistoriadebocacomarjugadoresjuanevaristo17190520131html Juan Evaristos biographyref